HB 502 Original 2026 Regular Session McCormick
Abstract: Requires the governing authority of the Caddo Parish to evaluate and provide
documentation of property taxes abated by each taxing entity before approving any
payment in lieu of taxes (P.I.L.O.T.) program and requires approval of certain Caddo
Parish officials before the program may be used.
Present law specifies that the Caddo Bossier Parishes Port Commission exercises its powers
within the port area consisting of Caddo and Bossier parishes, excluding certain docks,
landings, wharves, and river operation businesses in use on Nov. 8, 1966.
Proposed law retains present law and requires the governing authority of Caddo Parish to
fully evaluate and provide documentation of property taxes abated by each taxing entity
before approving the use of a P.I.L.O.T. program in the parish.
Proposed law requires that the documentation be provided to the political subdivisions listed
in proposed law, who must use the information to determine whether to approve the
program.
Proposed law authorizes the commission to use the P.I.L.O.T. program in Caddo Parish only
upon approval of the Caddo Parish Sheriff, the Caddo Parish Commission, and the Caddo
Parish School Board, with each entity independently determining whether to approve the
abatement of its respective portion of property taxes, and the Caddo Parish Commission is
additionally able to approve abatements for other local entities except the Sheriff and School
Board, allowing a project to proceed with any portions approved even if others are denied.
(Amends R.S. 34:3160(A))
